Package: hierarchicell
Title: Simulating Cell-Type Specific and Hierarchical Single-Cell RNA-Seq Data
Version: 1.0.1
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Kip",
           family = "Zimmerman",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "kdzimmer@wakehealth.edu",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-2943-6612"))
Description: A simulation engine that estimates important parameters from single-cell RNA-seq expression 
    counts to simulate expression data that are cell-type specific and hierarchical in nature. The simulated 
    data can then be used to compute power and type 1 error calculations under a variety of conditions. The 
    package consists of four important categories of functions: data loading and cleaning, empirical 
    estimation of distributions, simulating expression data, and computing power or type 1 error. 
    KD Zimmerman, MA Espeland, CD Langefeld (2020) <doi:10.1101/2020.01.15.906248>.
